{"key":"processedPost-11575389","value":{"id":11575389,"first":11575377,"last":11575410,"when":1259852123,"utime":"12/03/09 04:55 PM","content":"Just about any grain you can find that isn't too starchy will work.&nbsp; You'll just have to experiment with what you can find locally.&nbsp; If it's too starchy, the grains will all stick together and be hard for the mycelium to colonize and also to break up later.&nbsp; Rye berries are the grain of choice because they aren't starchy at all, thus the grains remain loose.&nbsp; Too bad you can't get it there.<br />RR","title":"Re: Does anyone have any experience with 'Red Cargo Rice' for straight grain?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}